Preheat your oven to 200℃. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to
peel!). Put on a large #roasting tray{}, drizzle with @oil{1%splash} and season with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Toss together, spread out in a single layer
and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips. Trim, then coarsely grate the @carrot{1}(coarsely grated) (no need to peel!).
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When
hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes},
breaking it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks.

Add the carrot and pepper to the pan along with the @Mexican spice{1} and garlic.
Cook for a couple of minutes then add the @tomato passata{1}, @water{150%ml} and
@beef stock powder{1}. Stir and bring to the boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat
and simmer until the sauce is thick and tomatoey, ~{10-12%minutes}, stirring
occasionally.

While everything is cooking, drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}, then
stir into the beef. Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}(grated), trim the
@spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced) and thinly slice, keep to one side.
Cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges for squeezing over.

When the wedges are ready, transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and put your #grill{} on
high. When your beef mix is thick and saucy, season to taste with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}. Spoon it on top of the wedges. Sprinkle on the Cheddar cheese
and pop under the grill. Grill until the cheese is golden and bubbly,
~{2-3%minutes}. Get ready to serve.

Finish with a sprinkle of spring onion and lime wedges for squeezing. Pop in the
middle of the table and dig in.

> Have plenty of napkins close to hand, it could get messy...!